---
import { ExternalLink } from "lucide-solid/icons/index";
import DevpadLogo from "../components/solid/DevpadLogo";
import GithubLogin from "../components/solid/GithubLogin";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="devpad">
  <body>
    <main
      class="landing-page"
      style="display: grid; gap: 100px; width: 80vw; max-width: 1000px; justify-items: center"
    >
      <div></div>
      <br />
      <section id="hero" style="width: 100%">
        <h1 class="flex-row" style="gap: 20px; justify-content: center;">
          <DevpadLogo size={48} />
          <span style="font-size: 3rem;">devpad</span>
        </h1>
        <div style="height: 75px"></div>
        <div
          style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; justify-content: center;"
        >
          <div
            style="width: 100%; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; justify-content: center; align-items: center;"
          >
            <p style="font-size: 1.5rem">
              scan & track <code>@todo</code> comments
            </p>
            <p
              style="margin-top: -19px; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-tertiary)"
            >
              & way more
            </p>
            <div style="font-size: 1.2rem">
              <GithubLogin size={30} client:load />
            </div>
          </div>
          <img src="/hero-scan.png" alt="Scan codebase into tasks" />
        </div>
      </section>
      <br />
      <section
        id="projects"
        style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 25px;"
      >
        <h2 style="text-align: center">project management</h2>
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px;">
          <p>
            devpad offers a dead simple yet powerful way to manage your
            ever-increasing list of projects. with options for visibility,
            development progress, and the abiltiy to specify separate github &
            deployment links for each project, all of your projects can be
            managed in a single place. when linking to a github repo, devpad
            offers the ability to scan the codebase for tasks, automatically
            updating, creating or deleting tasks for you.
            <a style="margin-top: 10px;" class="flex-row" href="/project">
              <span>projects</span>
              <ExternalLink />
            </a>
          </p>
          <img src="/project-creator.png" alt="project creator dialog" />
          <img src="/project-api.png" alt="devpad projects api" />
          <p>
            when all your projects have been setup, you can make use of devpad's
            built-in api to query your projects, perfect for integrating with
            your portfolio website, or other projects. with this api, you can
            build your own extensions, keeping this application as the only
            place to manage your projects.
            <a style="margin-top: 10px;" class="flex-row" href="/docs">
              <span>api docs</span>
              <ExternalLink />
            </a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section
        id="tasks"
        style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 25px;"
      >
        <h2 style="text-align: center">task management</h2>
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px;">
          <p>
            keeping track of everything you need to do for a project is a pain.
            devpad offers a simple way to add new tasks, attach them to a
            project, and add a summary, description, give due dates and assign
            priorities. when integrated with the project manager, you can update
            these tasks automatically directly from the comments in your
            codebase, with just enough user verification to make sure everything
            is how you want it.
            <a style="margin-top: 10px;" class="flex-row" href="/todo">
              <span>tasks</span>
              <ExternalLink />
            </a>
          </p>
          <img src="/task-view.png" alt="Task grid view" />
          <img src="/scan-update.png" alt="Update dialog for task scanning" />
          <p>
            the task editor allows you to assign tags to each tasks, allowing
            for powerful searching & filtering. similar to the project manager,
            all of this data is available via the built-in api, allowing you to
            hook into your task list from anywhere. the possibilties are
            endless.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <!-- TODO: add testimonials 

        id="testimonials"
        style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 25px;"
      >
        <h2 style="text-align: center">testimonials</h2>
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px;">
          
        </div>
      </section>
      <br /> -->
      <section
        id="how-it-works"
        style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 25px;"
      >
        <h2 style="text-align: center">how it works</h2>
        <div
          style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: 10px 20px; justify-items: center;"
        >
          <img src="/import-project.png" alt="Import project from github" />
          <img src="/check-for-updates.png" alt="Scan repo for updates" />
          <img src="/scan-updates.png" alt="Accept updates from scan" />
          <p>1. import project</p>
          <p>2. check for updates</p>
          <p>3. accept updates</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <br />
      <section
        id="end"
        style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 25px; align-items: center;"
      >
        <h2 style="text-align: center">let's get started</h2>
        <GithubLogin size={30} client:load />
      </section>
      <br />
      <br />
    </main>
    <footer>
      <p>Â© 2025 devpad</p>
    </footer>
  </body>
</Layout>
